That marks the final lacrosse game for the Aces in 2017. Thanks to everyone for following along, reading and sharing.
This was a season to remember for Ramapo. The Green Raiders went 17-6 and were Group 2 champions. pic.twitter.com/NChwN7Oycf
Boys lacrosse final score: Ramapo suffers a 10-4 loss to Delbarton in the Tournament of Champions semifinal.
Boys lacrosse: The score may not show this, but Johnny Caponi has really battled in goal for Ramapo tonight. Only a junior, too.
Boys lacrosse: Ramapo's Andrew Robbins gets his second goal of the game and 67th of the season. Delbarton leads 9-4 with 5:30 left.
SB: IC wins it, 13-1. Will be IHA vs. IC in the first-ever TOC final. That's pretty cool.
SB: IC will take a 13-1 (!) lead into the bottom of the fifth.
Boys lacrosse score after three: Delbarton 8, Ramapo 3.
SB: Two-run double by Angela Lignelli makes it 13-1 in the fifth. She's 3-for-4 with two doubles and four RBI.
Boys lacrosse: Delbarton is starting to take over in the third Q. Two quick goals by Colin Crowley make it 7-3 over the Green Raiders.
Boys lacrosse: Ramapo's Trevor Ivanow scores and Delbarton's Tom Schelling answers on the other end. 5-3 Delbarton at 6:49 in the third.
Boys lacrosse: Jack Griffin gets a goal for Ramapo by cutting in from the crease and taking a pass from Ryan Sisti. 4-2 Delbarton.
SB: Now an RBI groundout by Brianna Ramos makes it 11-1 IC in the top of the fourth.
SB: Kayla Robert with a sacrifice fly. 10-1 Immaculate Conception.
SB: Every Immaculate Conception batter has at least one hit.
SB: Immaculate Conception has 14 hits tonight. And the entire lineup has produced.
SB: The hits keep on coming. Jaden Farhat with a two-run double to deep LCF. Immaculate Conception up, 9-1 in the fourth.
SB: Angela Lignelli leads off the fourth with a single to left.
Boys lacrosse: Ramapo trails 4-1 at the half. Delbarton got a goal with one second left from Colin Crowley.
SB: IC up 7-1 going to the bottom of the third. This isn't news, but the Blue Wolves can flat-out hit.
Boys lacrosse: 3-1 Delbarton late in the second quarter. Ramapo is doing a good job weathering the storm with Caponi sharp in net.
SB: Mosley two-run single for IC. Blue Wolves now up, 7-1.
Boys lacrosse: Ramapo goal. Who else but Andrew Robbins? Cuts the lead to 2-1.
SB: 1-2-3 bottom of the second for Caylee English. IC 5, Egg Harbor 1.
SB: Inning ends with a groundout. IC scores five runs in the inning. 5-1 Blue Wolves going to the bottom of the second.
Boys lacrosse: Ramapo down 2-0 to Delbarton after one. Four saves by Johnny Caponi for the Green Raiders.
SB: And then Angela Lignelli hit a double to deep CF. Fredette scores. 5-1 Blue Wolves.
SB: Fredette takes off for second but the catcher's throw goes into the OF. Ramos scores on the error.
SB: Gabby Fredette RBI infield single makes it 3-1 IC.
SB: IC makes it 2-1 as Brianna Ramos bunts for an RBI infield single. Ash Callahan then singles to LF. Bases loaded. Still no outs.
Boys lacrosse: Delbarton jumps up 2-0 in the first quarter.
SB: Kayla Robert RBI single to right. All tied up at 1-1.
SB: Now a double from Jaden Farhat puts runners on second and third with no outs.
SB: Faith Camilleri leads off the top of the second with a single to center.
SB: Caylee English gets a strikeout to end the inning and escape further trouble. EH 1, IC 0 going to the second.
Boys lacrosse: Delbarton scores off the faceoff. 1-0 Green Wave a few minutes in.
SB: Back-to-back doubles for Egg Harbor in the first gives the Eagles a 1-0 lead.
SB: The second semifinal between IC and Egg Harbor is underway. Winner gets IHA in Friday's final.
Ramapo has taken the field. The Green Raiders (17-5) are looking to make their first Tournament of Champions final. pic.twitter.com/AeJv1vYun2
